Yeah—it absolutely breaks out like love does. “Luck” isn’t one thing; it’s a cluster of mechanisms that feel similar but operate differently.

Here’s a clean, grounded taxonomy you can actually use:

⸻

Core 4 Types of Luck (baseline model)

1. Blind Luck (Pure Chance)
	•	Random events you don’t influence
	•	Example: winning a lottery, random encounter

Control: none
Strategy: exposure (more tickets, more reps)

⸻

2. Motion Luck (Luck from Action)
	•	You create opportunities by moving, trying, exploring
	•	Example: meeting someone because you went somewhere new

Control: high (through volume of attempts)
Strategy: increase surface area

⸻

3. Preparation Luck (Skill Meets Opportunity)
	•	You’re ready when randomness shows up
	•	Example: recognizing a business opportunity others miss

Control: very high
Strategy: build capability + pattern recognition

⸻

4. Identity Luck (Luck Finds You)
	•	Your reputation, identity, or positioning attracts outcomes
	•	Example: people bring you opportunities

Control: indirect but powerful
Strategy: become the kind of node luck routes through

⸻

Yes—it does break down further (like love)

If you zoom in, each type splits into subtypes:

⸻

Under Blind Luck
	•	Temporal luck (right time)
	•	Spatial luck (right place)
	•	Collision luck (random intersections)

⸻

Under Motion Luck
	•	Exploration luck (trying new domains)
	•	Network luck (meeting people)
	•	Volume luck (more attempts = more hits)

⸻

Under Preparation Luck
	•	Recognition luck (seeing what others miss)
	•	Execution luck (acting faster/better)
	•	Synthesis luck (connecting ideas across domains)

⸻

Under Identity Luck
	•	Reputation gravity (pulling opportunities)
	•	Narrative luck (your story attracts outcomes)
	•	Trust routing (people choose you specifically)

⸻

The hidden layer (most people miss this)

There’s also:

5. Perception Luck (Interpretation Layer)
	•	Same event → different meaning → different outcome

Example:
	•	One person sees failure
	•	Another sees signal → pivots → wins later

This is where your “feels like vs is” idea fits perfectly

⸻

Pantheon compression
	•	Blind = environment randomness
	•	Motion = Spider expanding graph
	•	Preparation = Hound sharpening detection
	•	Identity = you become a hub node
	•	Perception = Mirror interpreting reality

